Interface DataInserter

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    DataInserterAbstract, LecturerDataInserterImpl, StudentDataInserterImpl

    public interface DataInserter
    The base template for common SQL data insertion and update process for users.
    Author:
    Ryan Gilera

    • Method Detail

      • insertNewComment

        void insertNewComment(AppEvent.SubmitNewCommentEvent event)
        Inserts new comment into the database. If successfully inserted a new row, a new notification based on the previous event is created. This method is triggered by the AppEventBus. An error is displayed to the user when an SQLException occurs.
        Parameters:
        event - a custom event object defined in AppEvent class

      • insertNewNote

        void insertNewNote(AppEvent.SubmitNewNoteEvent event)
        Inserts new note associated comment into the database. If successfully inserted a new row, new notification based on the previous event is created. This method is triggered by the AppEventBus. An error is displayed to the user when an SQLException occurs.
        Parameters:
        event - a custom event object defined in AppEvent class

      • updateNoteIsReadWhenClicked

        void updateNoteIsReadWhenClicked(AppEvent.UpdateNoteIsReadWhenClickEvent event)
        Updates the note status when clicked depending on the user type. This method is triggered by the AppEventBus. An error is displayed to the user when an SQLException occurs.
        Parameters:
        event - a custom event object defined in AppEvent class
